## `pub fn parse_path(path: &str) -> Result<Vec<String>>`
<!-- checksum: rust-paths-2 -->

### Purpose
Parse an absolute path string into a `Vec<String>` of reference-token components. Same semantics as the Python version; Rust signature returns `Result<Vec<String>>` instead of raising exceptions.

### Preconditions
- `path` is a `&str` (UTF-8 by Rust invariant).

### Postconditions
- If `path == "/"`: returns `Ok(vec![])`.
- Otherwise if `path` starts with `/`:
  - Strip leading `/` and an optional trailing `/`.
  - Split on `/`, collect into `Vec<String>`.
  - Each component passes the validation below.
  - Return the vec.
- Each component satisfies: non-empty, not `"."`, not `".."`, no embedded NUL, and `component.len() ≤ NAME_MAX` (bytes — since `&str` is UTF-8, `.len()` is byte length).

### Failure Modes
- `path == ""`: `Err(Error::PathSyntax("path is empty".into()))`.
- `path.len() > PATH_MAX`: `Err(Error::PathSyntax(format!("path exceeds PATH_MAX ({})", PATH_MAX)))`.
- `!path.starts_with('/')`: `Err(Error::PathSyntax(format!("path must be absolute, got {path:?}")))`.
- Empty component (double slash): `Err(Error::PathSyntax(...))`.
- Component `.` or `..`: `Err(Error::PathSyntax(...))`.
- Component contains `\0`: `Err(Error::PathSyntax(...))`.
- Component length > `NAME_MAX`: `Err(Error::NameTooLong(...))`.

### Invariants
- Pure function; deterministic; no I/O.
- Because `&str` is guaranteed valid UTF-8, the Python "bytes path" rejection becomes compile-time: callers can't pass non-UTF-8 bytes without explicit conversion.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use crate::errors::{Error, Result};

pub const PATH_MAX: usize = 4096;
pub const NAME_MAX: usize = 255;

pub fn parse_path(path: &str) -> Result<Vec<String>> {
    if path.is_empty() {
        return Err(Error::PathSyntax("path is empty".into()));
    }
    if path.len() > PATH_MAX {
        return Err(Error::PathSyntax(
            format!("path exceeds PATH_MAX ({PATH_MAX})"),
        ));
    }
    if !path.starts_with('/') {
        return Err(Error::PathSyntax(
            format!("path must be absolute, got {path:?}"),
        ));
    }
    if path == "/" {
        return Ok(Vec::new());
    }

    // Strip leading '/', plus one trailing '/' if present.
    let trimmed = &path[1..];
    let trimmed = trimmed.strip_suffix('/').unwrap_or(trimmed);

    let mut components = Vec::new();
    for part in trimmed.split('/') {
        if part.is_empty() {
            return Err(Error::PathSyntax(
                format!("empty component in path {path:?}"),
            ));
        }
        if part == "." || part == ".." {
            return Err(Error::PathSyntax(
                format!("'.' and '..' are not permitted: {path:?}"),
            ));
        }
        if part.contains('\0') {
            return Err(Error::PathSyntax(
                format!("embedded NUL in path {path:?}"),
            ));
        }
        if part.len() > NAME_MAX {
            return Err(Error::NameTooLong(
                format!("component {part:?} exceeds NAME_MAX ({NAME_MAX})"),
            ));
        }
        components.push(part.to_string());
    }
    Ok(components)
}
```

### Test Strategy

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn parse_root_returns_empty() { assert_eq!(parse_path("/").unwrap(), Vec::<String>::new()); }

    #[test]
    fn parse_single() { assert_eq!(parse_path("/foo").unwrap(), vec!["foo"]); }

    #[test]
    fn parse_multiple() { assert_eq!(parse_path("/a/b/c").unwrap(), vec!["a", "b", "c"]); }

    #[test]
    fn parse_unicode() {
        assert_eq!(parse_path("/café").unwrap(), vec!["café"]);
        assert_eq!(parse_path("/日本語").unwrap(), vec!["日本語"]);
    }

    #[test]
    fn rejects_empty() { assert!(parse_path("").is_err()); }

    #[test]
    fn rejects_relative() {
        assert!(parse_path("foo").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("./foo").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("../foo").is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn rejects_dot_components() {
        assert!(parse_path("/a/./b").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("/a/../b").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("/.").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("/..").is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn rejects_double_slash() {
        assert!(parse_path("//").is_err());
        assert!(parse_path("/a//b").is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn trailing_slash_normalized() {
        assert_eq!(parse_path("/foo/").unwrap(), vec!["foo"]);
        assert_eq!(parse_path("/a/b/").unwrap(), vec!["a", "b"]);
    }

    #[test]
    fn rejects_embedded_nul() {
        assert!(parse_path("/foo\0bar").is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn name_too_long_boundary() {
        let ok = "a".repeat(255);
        assert_eq!(parse_path(&format!("/{ok}")).unwrap(), vec![ok.clone()]);
        let too_long = "a".repeat(256);
        assert!(matches!(parse_path(&format!("/{too_long}")),
                         Err(Error::NameTooLong(_))));
    }

    #[test]
    fn name_byte_length_not_char() {
        // "é" is 2 bytes UTF-8
        let short = "é".repeat(127);  // 254 bytes, OK
        assert!(parse_path(&format!("/{short}")).is_ok());
        let too_long = "é".repeat(128);  // 256 bytes, NameTooLong
        assert!(matches!(parse_path(&format!("/{too_long}")),
                         Err(Error::NameTooLong(_))));
    }

    #[test]
    fn path_too_long() {
        let comps = vec!["a"; 2048];
        let p = format!("/{}", comps.join("/"));
        assert!(parse_path(&p).is_ok());
        let comps = vec!["a"; 2049];
        let p = format!("/{}", comps.join("/"));
        assert!(matches!(parse_path(&p), Err(Error::PathSyntax(_))));
    }
}
```

